      {
        "id": 4241626,
        "name": "Howard Cooper",
        "username": "Howard_Cooper",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/howard_cooper/{size}/700_2.png",
        "created_at": "2024-01-06T15:22:28.159Z",
        "cooked": "<p>I know that in Burgundy there can be plots of land that are gems but are not that well known.  In Pernand-Vergelesses, I long ago learned about Ile des Vergelesses and what outstanding wines Chandon de Briailles makes from this vineyard.</p>\n<p>Two white Burgundies I had this past year from En Caradeux made me wonder if I had found another gem or whether I just am lucky.  First, this past summer when I tasted at Armand Heitz I had a 2020 where we had a very nice wine from the vineyard.  In fact, my wife fell in love with this and thought it was better than a few more expensive whites we had there.  I, not being humble, thought it was a very nice wine (and bought HER a couple of bottles) but wondered whether it would improve with age (despite having had a few whites from PV from Chandon de Briailles that aged nicely).  Reason - I had never heard of the vineyard.</p>\n<p>I began to feel differently about my wife\u2019s ability to taste young wine, and about the vineyard and my prejudices, later last year when I drank a 2013 PYCM from the vineyard at my group\u2019s wine dinner (sheepishly I must admit that the wine came from my cellar).  It really blew me away - surprisingly it also blew away a 2013 PYCM Saint-Aubin 1er Cru Les Perri\u00e8res Blanc.  So, I became more interested in the vineyard.</p>\n<p>Then, a few months ago, in the wine of the year thread, Kevin Diffley listed as one of his favorites of the year a 2017 Domaine Chanson Pernand Vergelesses Les Caradeux.</p>\n<p>With this addition, I really became even more curious about the vineyard - excellent wines, three producers, three vintages, certainly the vineyard has to have something to do with the quality.</p>\n<p>So, does anyone here know much about the vineyard.  Is it thought of generally as punching above its weight or have we just been lucky?  Could my wife have been right???</p>",
        "post_number": 1,
        "post_type": 1,
        "posts_count": 7,
        "updated_at": "2024-01-06T15:24:24.555Z",
        "reply_count": 0,
