      {
        "id": 4241989,
        "name": "Rick Allen",
        "username": "Rick_Allen",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/rick_allen/{size}/90255_2.png",
        "created_at": "2024-01-06T21:59:55.702Z",
        "cooked": "<p>The vineyard sits across the ravine from En Charlemagne, facing pretty much due east.  The upper quarter of the vineyard is designated Village.  The Premier Cru portion is 14ha and the Village portion is 5ha.  I thought ownership information might be interesting, but Kramer didn\u2019t break down ownership in Pernand-Verglesses outside of Charlemagne.  From Landrieu-Lussigny &amp; Pitiot, \u201cWe also wonder whether \u201cCaradeux\u201d would not be the transcription of the nominal group \u201cChar a Boeufs\u201d or \u201cOxcart\u201d.  The lowest parcel of this lieu-dit stretches along the D18 road which goes up to Echevronne\u2026  \u2026This ancient cart track taken by ox drawn wagons may have given its name to this lieu-dit.\u201d</p>",
